# ---- Python ----
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ---- Virtual environments ----
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ---- Environment / secrets ----
.env
.env.*
# The key TEMPLATE is committed; only files holding real keys are ignored.
!.env.example

# ---- IDE (JetBrains / VS Code) ----
# Ignore IDE *state* (workspace.xml, caches, per-machine SDK paths) but SHIP the run
# configurations: the numbered ladder 0_estimate -> 15_judge_aggregate IS the pipeline, and
# the brief asks for something runnable from scratch. Note this must ignore .idea's CONTENTS,
# not the directory — git will not descend into an ignored directory to find the negation.
.idea/*
!.idea/runConfigurations/
.vscode/

# ---- OS cruft ----
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ---- Raw data (large binary PDFs) ----
# The 13 hospital source PDFs (fictional ground truth) ARE committed — the pipeline
# needs them and they exist nowhere public. The 15 medical PDFs are large, public
# CDC/ECDC reports used only as RAG distractors: re-download rather than bloat git.
data/raw/medical/

# ---- Trained model artifacts (LoRA adapters + tokenizers) ----
# This rule used to cover only the .tar.zst archive — and the EXTRACTED adapter was then
# committed anyway, all 160 MB of it, which is over GitHub's 100 MB per-file hard limit and
# made the repo unpushable. The rule now covers the whole directory (~222 MB).
#
# Weights are build artifacts, not deliverables. Nothing is lost:
#   * the Qwen ladder retrains from scratch in 13.2 minutes for $0.00
#         python -m contenders finetune --backend local
#   * the 8B rung is the documented one-off $4 Together job
#         python -m contenders finetune --backend together --train-only
#   * results/finetune_jobs.json keeps the training time, cost, VRAM and model ids — the
#     numbers the report actually cites survive in git; only the weights do not.
#
# What IS committed is every artifact the comparison rests on: the 1,000 answers, the 1,000
# judge verdicts, the master table, and the frozen FAISS index.
models/